<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="622" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Tyler</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-08-31"><hi rend="italic">August 31,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 35.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 63, of the 23d ultimo, reporting further action taken by
                            you to secure the apprehension and punishment of the murderers of Doctor
                            Labaree.</p>
                        <p>The Department commends your course in the matter, and enjoins your
                            continued discreet energy in pressing the matter.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>